    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="520"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d520">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Colonel <persName type="from">Marshall S. Carter</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="18" xml:id="d520fn18">General Marshall’s representative in
                        Washington.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">to General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-07">7 June
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>90515. Following message transmitted to you at request of Mr. John Carter
                        Vincent<note n="19" xml:id="d520fn19">Director of the Office of Far Eastern
                        Affairs.</note> in reply to your 788 of May 29: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Appreciate very much your giving me explanation contained in your 788 of
                            May 29. Actually the statement to which you refer was <pb facs="1007"
                                n="995" xml:id="pg_995"/> deleted by me from the script day before
                            broadcast was given but too late to have NBC release altered.
                            Incidentally, there were other substantial deletions and alterations in
                            the script before the broadcast was given, which have been forwarded to
                            you by Carter. Best regards, Vincent.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
